        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Support z.ai BigModel team usage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Support z.ai BigModel team usage through saved token accounts in Settings, CLI, and config using `usageScope: team`, `organizationId`, and `workspaceID`.\n- Route z.ai team quota/model/hourly requests with the BigModel team selectors and headers while personal accounts clear team context.\n- Add `codexbar config set-api-key --provider zai ... --usage-scope team ...` plus focused CLI/config tests.\n- Keep z.ai docs concise and add missing localized labels for Team mode / Organization ID.\n\n## Why\nBigModel team Coding Plan usage can return empty personal data unless queried with the team selector and BigModel organization/project headers. The token-account path supports personal and team z.ai accounts without adding browser-cookie auth or a global `Z_AI_USAGE_SCOPE` setting.\n\n## Notes\n- z.ai team scope is account-level only; `Z_AI_USAGE_SCOPE` is not read or documented.\n- Team accounts require single-line BigModel organization and project IDs.\n- The release-owned `CHANGELOG.md` entry was removed; release-note context stays in this PR body.\n- Existing legacy z.ai Keychain token migration remains only for old API-token storage migration.\n\n## Live Proof\n- Redacted local BigModel CN team-token probe:\n  - Command: `swift run CodexBarCLI usage --provider zai --account <team-account> --format json`\n  - Result: `source: api`, `provider: zai`\n  - Returned z.ai windows: primary `1 week window`, secondary `Monthly` (MCP), tertiary `5 hours window`\n  - Token, organization ID, and project ID were not printed or posted.\n- Team model/hourly request construction is covered by `ZaiBigModelTeamScopeTests` and `ZaiHourlyUsageTests`.\n\n## Screenshots/GIFs\n- Not included: visible changes are limited to Settings token-account fields/labels and are covered by descriptor/localization tests.\n\n## Test Plan\n- `swift test --filter CLIConfigCommandTests`\n- `swift test --filter LocalizationLanguageCatalogTests`\n- `make check`\n- `make test`\n- `git diff --check`",
